<title>USA: Mergers the only option for refiners, say analysts.</title>
<headline>Mergers the only option for refiners, say analysts.</headline>
<byline>David Chance</byline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Confronted with weak refining margins in the U.S. and Europe, oil companies have little choice but to merge downstream operations, say analysts.</p>
<p>On Monday, reports emerged that Amoco Corp and Mobil Corp would combine their U.S. downstream operations, hard on the heels of a Friday's confirmation of a deal between Ashland Inc and USX-Marathon Group.</p>
<p>&quot;There appears to be a realisation that these companies are not going to benefit substantially from margin improvements,&quot; said Schroder Wertheim analyst Philip Tendler.</p>
